gomodel:SYNGO_596  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The supplemental table S1 contains proteins identified in the PSD preparation (Synaptic junctional protein preparation).\nFor proteins coming from datasets derived from PSD (detergent-resistant synaptic junctions) preparations without defined selection / enrichment of the pre- or postsynaptic compartment we cannot assign these proteins to excitatory and/or inhibitory nor to the presynapse or / and postsynapse without further information.. Experimental description: \"Briefly, brains from adult mice (strain C57BL/6J; first experiment: 3-12 months of age; second experiment: 4-16 months; n ≥ 14 per experiment) were dissected;...\" P.683" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
